OL,3,CPolice and crime commissioners to be
OL,4,Cscrapped
OL,6,FPolice and crime commissioners in
OL,7,FEngland and Wales will be abolished,
OL,8,Fthe government has announced.
OL,10,FThe elected officials were first
OL,11,Fintroduced in 2012 and their
OL,12,Fresponsibilities include setting
OL,13,Fbudgets for their police forces and
OL,14,Fappointing the most senior officer `
OL,15,Fthe chief constable ` for their area.
OL,17,FMinisters plan to abolish the role in
OL,18,F2028 when the next elections are set
OL,19,Fto be held to save at least #100
OL,20,Fmillion and help fund neighbourhood
OL,21,Fpolicing.
